{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"1d6f79f2-bdb7-43c6-bb40-216f1763f42e","content":"Yes, you'll hit compatibility issues. MSTest v3 **dropped support** for two of your three target frameworks:\n\n| Target | MSTest v3 Support |\n|---|---|\n| `net462` | ✅ Supported (.NET Framework ≥ 4.6.2) |\n| `net5.0` | ❌ Dropped (end-of-life) |\n| `netcoreapp3.1` | ❌ Dropped (end-of-life) |\n\nMSTest v3 requires **.NET 6.0+** for the .NET Core side.\n\n**To migrate, you would need to:**\n\n1. **Update your target frameworks** — replace `net5.0` and `netcoreapp3.1` with supported versions (e.g., `net6.0`, `net8.0`).\n2. **Consolidate packages** — MSTest v3 offers a single `MSTest` meta-package that replaces `MSTest.TestFramework`, `MSTest.TestAdapter`, and `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk`.\n\nIf you still need to test against `netcoreapp3.1` or `net5.0`, you'll need to stay on MSTest v2 for those targets.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"caeb00b4-3d1b-4bbd-a8bc-8035af30327f","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user's project targets `net5.0`, `net462`, and `netcoreapp3.1`. MSTest v3 has dropped support for some older frameworks. Let me provide accurate information about compatibility issues.\n\nMSTest v3 (the `MSTest` meta-package or `MSTest.TestFramework` 3.x) dropped support for:\n- .NET Framework versions older than .NET Framework 4.6.2 — so `net462` should still be okay.\n- .NET Core 3.1 — this was dropped\n- .NET 5.0 — this was dropped\n\nMSTest v3 supports:\n\n\n- .NET Framework 4.6.2+ (so `net462` is fine)\n- .NET 6.0+ (meaning `net5.0` and `netcoreapp3.1` won't work)\n\nSo the user will run into compatibility issues with `net5.0` and `netcoreapp3.1` targets. MSTest v3 also consolidates everything into a single `MSTest` package rather than separate packages.","outputTokens":729,"requestId":"0BDA:3131A1:679A9C9:70DC67A:69F01EB0"},"id":"24711c58-d740-40c6-a496-12027741a703","timestamp":"2026-04-28T02:43:10.072Z","parentId":"9028eaff-5c1c-4b77-9362-c25529bcd2bc"}
